{"id":32130,"date":"2019-06-15T16:56:20","date_gmt":"2019-06-15T12:56:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=32130"},"modified":"2023-07-07T14:51:12","modified_gmt":"2023-07-07T10:51:12","slug":"not-belittle-any-sadaqah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/15\/not-belittle-any-sadaqah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Sadaqa: Do not belittle any charity, do not return insults"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Jurayy reported: I came to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, we are people of the desert. Teach us something with which Allah will benefit us.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Do not belittle any good deed, even pouring your leftovers into another\u2019s cistern, even speaking to your brother while smiling at him. Beware of trailing your garment; it is a form of vanity that Allah does not approve. If a man insults you with what he knows about you, do not insult him with what you know about him. Verily, you will have a reward, and the penalty is upon the one who spoke it.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Ibn H\u0323ibba\u0304n 522<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u062c\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u064d\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0647\u064f\u062c\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0645\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u062a\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064f\u0644\u0652\u062a\u064f \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\